headline: These 3 Warren Buffett Dividend Stocks Have Trounced the Market This Year. Can They Do It Again in 2025?
summary: Warren Buffett appears to be on track to beat the S&P 500 again in 2024, but not by much.  Berkshire Hathaway's shares are up year-to-date only around 3% more than the S&P.  Buffett has owned shares of American Express (NYSE: AXP) for decades.
